# Intuition
It is similar to the question [Merge Intervals](https://leetcode.com/problems/merge-intervals/) must try before doing this problem.

# Approach
Insert the new interval in and then the question becomes same as merge intervals.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(NLogN)

- Space complexity:O(2*N)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> insert(vector<vector<int>>& intervals, vector<int>& newInterval) {
        intervals.push_back({newInterval});
        sort(intervals.begin() , intervals.end());
        int j = 0 , n = intervals.size();
        for(int i = 1 ; i < n ; i++){
            if(intervals[j][1] >= intervals[i][0]){
                intervals[j][1] = max(intervals[j][1] , intervals[i][1]);
            }
            else{
                j++;
                intervals[j] = intervals[i];
            }
        }
        vector<vector<int>> ans;
        for(int i = 0 ; i <= j ; i++){
            ans.push_back(intervals[i]);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```
