# Approach:
My approach to solving the problem is as follows:

- Initialize an empty array for the left side of the intervals and another empty array for the right side.
- Iterate through each interval in the given intervals.
- Check if the current interval is completely before the new interval. If so, add it to the left array.
- Check if the current interval is completely after the new interval. If so, add it to the right array.
- If the current interval overlaps with the new interval, update the new interval's start and end values to cover both intervals.
- Finally, combine the left array, the new interval, and the right array to get the result.
# Complexity:
- Time complexity: The time complexity of this approach is O(n), where n is the number of intervals.
- Space complexity: The space complexity is also O(n), where n is the number of intervals.

# Code
```
function insert(intervals: number[][], newInterval: number[]): number[][] {
    let [newStart, newEnd] = newInterval, left = [], right = [];
    for( let int of intervals ){
        let [start, end] = int;
        if( end < newStart )left.push(int);
        else if( start > newEnd )right.push(int);
        else {
            newStart = Math.min(start, newStart);
            newEnd = Math.max(end, newEnd);
        }
    }
    return [...left, [newStart, newEnd], ...right]
};
```

